	   <tr><td colspan=2>In the last few days, my plans of making plat in Rathe off HG's has gotten blown all out of whack..<br><br>The entire zone has been converted to an ongoing quest/GM event called Nightfall Haunting.  Instead of bugs, there are spectre-type mobs, gargoyle-type mobs, and undead-dragon-type mobs.  In general, most things con at or below even to 35th Magician (lost 36th from the Blood Reaver... Jumped clear out of my equipment 10 times *sighs*).  For the most part, pretty easy.. with a lot of exp-greens and low blues.  <br><br>There are named spectres/gargs/etc which seem to have a better rate of drop on all items, but the entire zone is randomized for drops.  <br><br>The downside (and cause of MANY train-related deaths) is the Blood Reaver... about twice the size of the (apparently) 33-37 bloodbone drakes, which current wisdom states is a 60th Dragon (spells resisted unless cast in Melee range, 500 AOE cold effect, dragonfear, Immune to root/slow, etc).  It seems to have a nack for chasing down characters on it's way to zone and totally offing the rez stations set up in rathe..<br><br>I can't vouch for other classes, but I know the 3 int-caster drops I've seen have been a bracelet, a robe (7 int, 20 mana, Gown of the something), and this 4-int sash.  <br><br>I have been told (not by a GM, player-rumor) that the event will continue until Monday, November 5th.  It can be paused (all mobs despawn, normal mobs for rathe appear) for 2 hours by completing the uber-quest (something to do with turning in talons, supposably to a rare spawn priest or somesuch).  I have not seen this happen because the drops come fairly quickly and there is much shouting of Item X at -xxxx by +yyyy.<br><br>Just remember, the Blood Reaver has gotten me 10 times in 2 days... and most of the time, I didn't even have time for a screenshot, if I saw it at all.  <br><br>Sagonene<br>Red Wolf Clan<br>35th Magician<br>Zeb server<br><br>PS - Got all but the sash... have a 4 int belt.. NEVER going back until the Rathe Mountains Pizza delivery HG's come back :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
